{#─ Per-finding PR comment template (one thread per finding). ──────

  This file is the default starting point for the bot's PR comments.
  The bot renders it once per finding and posts the result as a single
  ADO thread, with the finding's file + line attached so it shows up
  inline in the PR's "Files" tab. The bot does NOT post a doc-level
  summary — only the per-finding threads.

  Point `COMMENT_TEMPLATE_PATH` at this file (after copying it to e.g.
  `./comment.md` and editing) in your `.env`:

      COMMENT_TEMPLATE_PATH=./comment.md

  Available placeholders (all may be empty / null unless noted):

      {{ title }}            finding title
      {{ message }}          body text
      {{ severity }}         nit | minor | major | blocker
      {{ severity_label }}   "🔴 blocker" / "🟠 major" / "🟡 minor" / "💡 nit"
      {{ confidence }}       high | medium | low   (or "")
      {{ context_basis }}    diff-only | surrounding-code-read |
                             full-module-review   (or "")
      {{ suggestion }}       suggested fix         (or "")
      {{ file }}             source file           (or "")
      {{ line }}             line number           (or null)
      {{ key }}              raw dedupe key
      {{ marker }}           "prb:<key>"  — visible text, NOT the dedupe line
      {{ summary }}          PR-level review summary
      {{ evidence }}         dict with sub-fields:
        .whyNewInThisPr
        .whyNotIntentional
        .changedLines        (list → pipe through `| join_list`)
        .contextFilesRead    (list → pipe through `| join_list`)

  Custom filters:

      {{ x | join_list }}      list → ", "-joined string; None → ""
      {{ x | join_list("; ")}} custom separator
      {{ x | fence }}          smart-fenced code block (escapes inner ```)
      {{ x | fence("ts") }}    with language hint

  Invariants the formatter enforces (you don't have to handle these):

    * The dedupe marker `<!-- prb:<key> -->` is appended as the LAST
      line of every rendered body, on its own line. Do not hand-write
      it — the formatter strips and re-appends it.
    * If the template inlines `{{ marker }}` for display, that text
      (raw `prb:<key>`) is left alone. The dedupe line is still
      appended separately.
    * The body is truncated to fit the thread if needed; the marker
      line is always preserved.
    * Optional placeholders (anything that may be missing on a given
      finding) are guarded with `{% if X %}` rather than
      `{% if X is defined %}` — the formatter pre-populates missing
      fields with empty / null.

  Note on per-finding vs summary: this template renders ONE thread per
  finding. A PR-level summary comment was considered and dropped — the
  per-finding threads give ADO the file/line context it needs to attach
  each comment inline in the Files tab, which is the only way
  reviewers see findings next to the code they apply to.

─#}

**{{ severity_label }}** — {{ title }}
{% if file or line %}
📍 `{{ file if file else "(no file)" }}`{% if line %} · line {{ line }}{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% if confidence or context_basis %}
<sub>{% if confidence %}confidence: {{ confidence }}{% endif %}{% if confidence and context_basis %} · {% endif %}{% if context_basis %}basis: {{ context_basis }}{% endif %}</sub>
{% endif %}

{{ message }}
{% if evidence %}
{% set ev = evidence %}
{% if ev.whyNewInThisPr %}
> **Why this is introduced by this PR:** {{ ev.whyNewInThisPr }}
{% endif %}
{% if ev.whyNotIntentional %}
> **Why this is unlikely to be intentional:** {{ ev.whyNotIntentional }}
{% endif %}
{% if ev.changedLines %}
> **Affected lines:** {{ ev.changedLines | join_list }}
{% endif %}
{% if ev.contextFilesRead %}
> **Context read:** {{ ev.contextFilesRead | join_list }}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% if suggestion %}

**Suggested fix:**

{{ suggestion | fence }}
{% endif %}
